{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase penalties for repeat bike thieves",
        "additional_details": "Around 1,100 bikes stolen every day in the UK, and only 5% of those stolen are returned each year. We want the Government to take action to tackle bike theft.\r\n \r\nWhilst the UK Government has said it\u2019s seeking a \u2018golden age\u2019 for cycling, bike theft is still a major barrier preventing cyclists from using their bikes as transport.\r\n",
        "background": "We want the Government to increase legal penalties for people found guilty of repeated bike theft offences. These should involve increased fines and custodial sentences, and mandatory Criminal Behaviour Orders.",
